    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-09-10T17:05:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-09-10T17:05:00-05:00" n="376"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d376">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/9–1054: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Mission at the united Nations</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d376fn1">Drafted by the Assistant Secretary of State for
                        International Organization Affairs (<persName corresp="#p_KEYDMK1"
                            >Key</persName>), cleared by phone by Mr. <persName corresp="#p_KEYDMK1"
                            >Key</persName> with Assistant Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_ROBERTSONWS1">Robertson</persName>(<gloss target="#t_FE1"
                            >FE</gloss>) and Deputy Assistant Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_BARBOURW1">Barbour</persName> (<gloss target="#t_EUR1"
                            >EUR</gloss>), and signed by Assistant Secretary <persName
                            corresp="#p_KEYDMK1">Key</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-09-10T18:05:00-04:00"
                            >September 10, 1954—6:05 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>140. Re: <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> Presidency (<gloss target="#t_urtel1"
                        >urtel</gloss> 2 to Manila and Dulte 26): We of course want <persName
                        corresp="#p_WWPWWKNB1">Wan</persName> elected and feel that anything which
                    you can discreetly accomplish toward this end within limitations imposed by
                    Secretary in Dulte 26 September 8 and by our undertakings to Thai and Dutch
                        (<gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 68 to <gloss target="#t_USUN1"
                        >USUN</gloss>) will be helpful. You will of course fully appreciate
                    importance of avoiding any action which could be regarded as violative of those
                    undertakings.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SMITHWB1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
